===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `less` baraye baz kardane file-ha va didane matn dakhele anha, safhe be safhe, estefade mishavad.  Shoma mitoonid be asooni bala va paeen berid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `less +F filename` -->  📡 Donbale tagheerat real-time file bash (mesle `tail -f`)
    🔹 `less -N filename` -->  🔢 Namayesh shomare khat-ha
    🔹 `less -S filename` -->  ✂️  Khat-haye toolani ro ghat kone va be baghie khat nare (chop mikone).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ less myfile.txt

    🔹 Baz kardane `myfile.txt` ba `less`.

    $ less logfile.log +F

    🔹 Didane logfile be soorate real-time.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ less -N myfile.txt

    🔹 File `myfile.txt` ro baz mikone va shomare khat-ha ro ham namayesh mide.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `less` command is used to view the contents of a file, one page at a time.  It allows you to easily navigate up and down.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `less +F filename` --> 📡 Follow changes to the file in real-time (like `tail -f`)
    🔹 `less -N filename` --> 🔢 Display line numbers
    🔹 `less -S filename` --> ✂️ Chop long lines instead of wrapping them.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ less myfile.txt

    🔹 Open `myfile.txt` with `less`.

    $ less logfile.log +F

    🔹 View the logfile in real-time.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ less -N myfile.txt

    🔹 Opens the file `myfile.txt` and displays line numbers.